Generic plotting function for "qed_did" objects

plot.qed_did.Rd

This function serves as a generic plot method for objects of class "qed_did", a result of a call to qed_did.

# S3 method for qed_did
plot(qed_did, ...)

Arguments

qed_did

an object of class "qed_did"

Value

a ggplot object visualizing trend lines between the pre-treatment period and the post-treatment period amongst the treatment and control groups. The points signify mean values of the dependent variable pre-treatment and post-treatment.

Details

Edits can be made to the plots using ggplot functions (such as changes to axis ticks, labels, etc).

Examples


data(banks)
did <- qed_did("num_banks_in_business", "year", 1930,  "bank_district", "6th district", df = banks)
